From: Ondrej Jirman <megous@megous.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Apr 2019 02:48:30 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 04/29] drm: Remove redundant of_device_is_available check

This check is already performed by of_graph_get_remote_node. No
need to repeat it immediately after the call.

Signed-off-by: Ondrej Jirman <megous@megous.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/drm_of.c | 5 -----
 1 file changed, 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_of.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_of.c
index 6becf63..222632c 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_of.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_of.c
@@ -249,11 +249,6 @@ int drm_of_find_panel_or_bridge(const struct device_node *np,
 	if (!remote)
 		return -ENODEV;
 
-	if (!of_device_is_available(remote)) {
-		of_node_put(remote);
-		return -ENODEV;
-	}
-
 	if (panel) {
 		*panel = of_drm_find_panel(remote);
 		if (!IS_ERR(*panel))
